# [LAMPS](../wg/lamps.html)

## Summary

The LAMPS (Limited Additional Mechanisms for PKIX and SMIME) Working Group met at IETF 126 to discuss active working group drafts, potential new adoptions, and updates to cryptographic standards. The agenda covered updates to attestation freshness, certificate discovery, S/MIME Version 4.0 handling, one-signature certificates, parameterized SIGNED types, composite signatures, and FrodoKEM integrations. Due to constraints, the meeting proceeded at a brisk pace, leaving several topics to be further detailed on the mailing list.

